  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "System Application Engineer - WCAN",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Design, develop, and improve technical systems and prototypes.</p></li><li><p>Create and maintain procedures for manufacturing, testing, and operations.</p></li><li><p>Install, service, and maintain equipment or systems as required.</p></li><li><p>Train staff on assembly, testing, and operational processes.</p></li><li><p>Support software and hardware integration for smooth system performance.</p></li><li><p>Maintain documentation and provide recommendations for process or design improvements.</p></li><li><p>Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues, offering feedback for optimization.</p></li><li><p>Analyze system performance and suggest enhancements.</p></li><li><p>Travel as needed for evaluations, installations, and training.</p></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree or higher in Electrical Engineering or a related discipline.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in MS Office and quick to learn specialized software tools.</p></li><li><p>Preferably over 1 year of relevant experience in electrical engineering or related roles.</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in programming languages like C++, C#, or HDL</p></li><li><p>Strong organizational, communication, and interpersonal skills.</p></li><li><p>Ability to multitask and prioritize effectively.</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated, reliable, and accountable.</p></li><li><p>Excellent problem-solving skills with strong attention to detail.</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently or supervise project-based tasks when required.</p></li></ul><p><br /></p><p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p><p><br /></p><p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 20C0270</p><p>EA Personnel: Nyon Hock Sen (Aden)</p><p>EA Personnel Reg No: R24124070</p>",
